        "old_string": "/**\n * TaskFlow Pro — A task and order management system.\n *\n * Architecture:\n * - Service Layer: UserService, OrderService (business logic)\n * - Repository Layer: UserRepository, OrderRepository (data access via Repository pattern)\n * - Utility Layer: Database, Logger, Pagination (infrastructure)\n * - Event System: EventBus with typed events (decoupled communication)\n *\n * Key architectural decisions:\n * 1. Repository pattern for all data access (no direct DB calls from services)\n * 2. Event-driven notifications (services emit events, listeners handle side effects)\n */",
        "new_string": "/**\n * TaskFlow Pro — A task and order management system with event-driven notifications.\n *\n * Architecture:\n * - Service Layer: UserService, OrderService (business logic)\n * - Notification Layer: NotificationService, PreferencesService, NotificationHistoryService\n * - Adapter Layer: EmailAdapter, SmsAdapter, WebhookAdapter (channel-specific delivery)\n * - Repository Layer: UserRepository, OrderRepository, PreferencesRepository, NotificationLogRepository\n * - Utility Layer: Database, Logger, Pagination (infrastructure)\n * - Event System: EventBus with typed events (decoupled communication)\n *\n * Key architectural decisions:\n * 1. Repository pattern for all data access (no direct DB calls from services)\n * 2. Event-driven notifications (services emit events, NotificationService handles delivery)\n * 3. Pluggable adapters per channel implementing NotificationAdapter interface\n * 4. Opt-out preference model (no preferences = all notifications allowed)\n * 5. Full notification history/audit trail via NotificationHistoryService\n */"
